                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17296196" author="beobal" created="Fri, 5 Mar 2021 17:15:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve added the missing job to the template &amp;amp; regenerated the low, mid and high resource files. I&apos;ve also copied &lt;tt&gt;config.yml.LOWRES&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;config.yml&lt;/tt&gt;, which I should&apos;ve done in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16474&quot; title=&quot;Multiple python dtest failures after promoting protocol v5 from beta&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-16474&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-16474&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/compare/trunk...beobal:16489-trunk?expand=1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;patch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17296257" author="edimitrova" created="Fri, 5 Mar 2021 18:21:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=samt&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;samt&quot;&gt;samt&lt;/a&gt;, I made a pass and I have only one question, we don&apos;t have to patch&#160;utests_system_keyspace_directory for higher resources, they are fine with medium resources? I mean for LOWRES and MIIDRES probably we are good as that is how the tests were added initially. But I wasn&apos;t sure whether you guys want them on HIGHRES on your end?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Maybe it is a good idea to trigger one clean run?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17296404" author="edimitrova" created="Sat, 6 Mar 2021 01:13:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I ended up running CI as I was trying to fix one more issue which we thought it is a matter of line but it turned out it is not so I am going to open a new ticket for that one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;CI runs look similar to Jenkins:&lt;br/&gt;
MIDRES - &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra/668/workflows/fdc790c1-86ed-4132-9bd7-8f514e7d9574&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;JAVA8 &lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra/667/workflows/ace464c4-41eb-4ca5-8814-508e130a88b1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;JAVA11 &lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
HIGHRES - &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra/668/workflows/fdc790c1-86ed-4132-9bd7-8f514e7d9574&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;JAVA8 &lt;/a&gt; | &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra/668/workflows/6f361605-0da3-40e3-ba49-fd9eb0c6d324&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;JAVA11 &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17296415" author="edimitrova" created="Sat, 6 Mar 2021 02:15:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was thinking to commit the patch tonight but there is one thing I just saw.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;utest_system_keyspace_directory&lt;/em&gt; turns out to need approval to be started not only by&#160;&lt;em&gt;utest_system_keyspace_directory&lt;/em&gt; but also by&#160;&lt;em&gt;utests_fqltool&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For reference, please, check the line connections in the diagram from the &#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/ekaterinadimitrova2/cassandra/668/workflows/fdc790c1-86ed-4132-9bd7-8f514e7d957&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;JAVA8&lt;/a&gt;&#160;CI run&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I know this was set during the initial addition of the tests but I think it is wrong, we should be able to start them as unit tests in their own group. I don&apos;t think those have anything in common with the FQLtool. (CC &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=blerer&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;blerer&quot;&gt;blerer&lt;/a&gt;&#160;as an author to correct me in case I am wrong &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17297195" author="beobal" created="Mon, 8 Mar 2021 09:03:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, that&apos;s a bad copy pasta from me. I&apos;ve pushed fixed versions and I&apos;ll run through CI now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17297717" author="beobal" created="Mon, 8 Mar 2021 21:45:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added a fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16498&quot; title=&quot;Python upgrade DTests fail in CircleCI&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-16498&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-16498&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/compare/trunk...beobal:16489-trunk?expand=1&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;branch&lt;/a&gt; and re-ran Circle jobs. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/beobal/cassandra/250/workflows/38d3199f-bc21-48da-97f6-479ca24d8dad&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;JDK 8 &lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://app.circleci.com/pipelines/github/beobal/cassandra/250/workflows/1962796c-ac14-4854-89d9-2c12a4830c27&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;JDK 11&lt;/a&gt; both look good. Except for known failures from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16483&quot; title=&quot;ColumnFilter::toString doesn&amp;#39;t return a valid CQL fragment&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-16483&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-16483&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &amp;amp; one flaky repair test, all python tests are now passing. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17297813" author="edimitrova" created="Tue, 9 Mar 2021 03:28:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM, thank you!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17297930" author="beobal" created="Tue, 9 Mar 2021 08:12:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, committed to trunk in &lt;tt&gt;9943d4b3035c2c69cd28001254b743b5c494ab01&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
